David Beckham arrives for his hearing at the Bromley Magistrates Court on Thursday (May 9) in London, England. The 44-year-old retired athlete admitted to using his cell phone while driving his Bentley back in November, and thus, was given a six-month driving ban, the BBC reports. The incident occurred on November 21, 2018, when David was seen driving his car down Great Portland Street in central London while using his phone. He enlisted lawyer Nick Freeman to assist him in court.